net.proteusframework.ui.search

Class ComboBoxConstraint

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.search.AbstractPropertyConstraint
      • net.proteusframework.ui.search.SimpleConstraint
        • net.proteusframework.ui.search.ComboBoxConstraint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, PropertyConstraint, SearchConstraint

    public class ComboBoxConstraint
extends SimpleConstraint
    Combo box constraint for selecting from predefined text. This is used in place of a field component when specific strings are expected. There are two ways to use this object. The constructor with an "any" option may be used, in which case the values are rendered with default behavior and the "any" option may be included or not. (Included for backward compatibility.) Or, the constructor with a renderer may be used, in which case the "any" property is ignored; the option list may have a "null" element and the renderer must handle this explicitly. NOTE: If both anyOption and renderer are set, the anyOption will be ignored.
    Author:
    Greg Dick (greg@i2rd.com)
